# Walkthrough - Reconciliation Page Refactor

I have refactored the [ConciliacionPage.tsx](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/ConciliacionWeb/Frontend/src/pages/ConciliacionPage.tsx) to align with the application's Atomic Design system and unify the UI with the "GestiÃ³n de Movimientos" page.

## Changes

### 1. Unified UI & Atomic Design
-   **FiltrosReporte**: Integrated the [FiltrosReporte](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/ConciliacionWeb/Frontend/src/components/organisms/FiltrosReporte.tsx#53-160) organism to provide consistent filtering capabilities.
-   **Table Styling**: Updated the reconciliation table to match the visual style of the [MovimientosPage](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/ConciliacionWeb/Frontend/src/pages/MovimientosPage.tsx#13-499) (white background, rounded corners, shadow, consistent padding/fonts).
-   **Layout**: Ensured proper integration with the [MainLayout](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/ConciliacionWeb/Frontend/src/components/templates/MainLayout.tsx#9-22) (provided by [App.tsx](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/ConciliacionWeb/Frontend/src/App.tsx)).

### 2. New Filters
-   **Date Range**: Replaced the simple Year/Month dropdowns with the standard Date Range picker. The logic automatically derives the reconciliation month from the selected start date.
-   **Account Filter**: Added a specific "Cuenta" filter to allow viewing a single account or all accounts at once.

